    Understanding common design patterns can be critical for software developers, since these common patterns often take advantage of existing features in code to solve common problems. But while understanding how common problems are solved may prevent time from being wasted through reinventing the wheel, a lack of understanding why they are solved that way may cause unessasary grief when an alternative means of accomplishing the task is built into the language.
    
